window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>\"Hush, little witchling, don’t say a thing</p> <p>Daddy’s gonna take you to the faery ring...\"</p> <p>Niamh ‘Luxe’ Finnegan is trying to move on with her life after losing her last known family member to cancer. She takes over her aunt’s store, Hecate’s Boutique, and prepares to continue grad school, believing herself entirely alone in the world. Luxe’s parents vanished during a vacation two decades ago, leaving her without answers. But everything changes when Søren, a stranger who claims to know the truth about her parents, enters her store.</p> <p>Søren reveals truths about Luxe that change her life irrevocably. Her dormant magical abilities awaken as her world spirals. If the fae queen knew Luxe’s true identity, Luxe would be dead already. As it is, the queen is growing curious about Luxe, which means she is in danger.</p> <p>Fleeing with Søren, she embarks on a perilous journey, joined by two other high fae, Alistair and Calix. Surrounded by the three powerful fae males, Luxe finds herself in precarious situations concerning both their lives and their hearts. Together, they attempt to unlock her magical potential, as they unravel a prophecy about the fae monarchy and avoid the queen’s clutches.</p> <p>In this first book of Luxe's Lullaby Trilogy, Luxe must accept her heritage and navigate her burgeoning powers, in order to save the only family she has left.</p> <p>Duet narration performed by Paige Reisenfeld and PJ Freebourn.</p>"; 
